snippet.title: Buffalo snowstorm: Residents cope with blizzard, as more snow on the way
snippet.description:
A dangerous lake-effect snowstorm has paralyzed a large area of New York State, with two feet of snow on the ground already and more on the way in the Buffalo region and surrounding area.

Global's chief meteorologist Anthony Farnell is on the ground in Buffalo, N.Y., where he details the frosty condition and speaks with residents on how they're coping with the deluge of snow.

"I am just amazed. I have never, ever seen snow like this in my entire life," one resident said.

The snow band is expected to shift north into the Niagara region of Ontario on Saturday morning, before more snow arrives on Sunday. 

For more info, please go to https://globalnews.ca/news/9289146/buffalo-snowstorm-blizzard-new-york-lake-effect-snow-photos/
